cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.GR, cs.SC, cs.SY. 

The paper deals with computational geometry problems related to polygons and circles, which suggests that it would likely fall under cs.CG (Computational Geometry) category. The use of a linear-time algorithm also suggests that it could be related to data structures (cs.DS). The problem of finding the largest circle under certain constraints could also be related to geometric reasoning (cs.GR) and optimization (cs.SC). Finally, the use of point and line constraints could suggest a connection to control systems (cs.SY).
